report.measDesc: The dataset is converted to file geodatabase (FGDB) format using tools in ArcGIS. The geometry is checked, and if needed repaired.
After processing, the dataset is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

The World Base Map was derived using Landsat 8, Landsat 7 (Global Land Survey (GLS) 2000 and GLS 2005), and SRTM (Shuttle Radar Topography Mission) as a global base. Landsat 7 provided the horizontal positional accuracy of +/- 50 meters 90% CE, and SRTM ensured that features appropriately fit the topography (i.e., rivers flowed through valleys).

datasetSeries.seriesName: A subset of World Base Map.

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Extracted the FGDB feature class from the subset of World Base Map. Deleted all fields except ISO_CC, NAME, ICAO, and IATA. Made the NAME field title case. Made the values of the ICAO field blanks that do not have a unique four-character ICAO code.
